[2] Possible California case
Date: Fri 27 Jul 2007
Source: San Diego North County Times (CA) [edited]
<http://www.nctimes.com/articles/2007/07/28/news/sandiego/15_59_907_27_07.txt>

State and county health officials said Fri 27 Jul 2007 that a
51-year-old San Diego County woman had been hospitalized and
diagnosed with botulism, but they were not sure if the woman got sick
from any of the dozens of brands of canned foods recalled recently.
State public health spokeswoman Lea Brooks said health workers were
still trying to determine if the woman, who has recovered and been
sent home, might have gotten sick from eating Castleberry Food
Company products.
Neither state nor county officials would say what part of the county
the woman lived in. They said she was hospitalized for 10 days about
a week after buying and eating Kroger chili with beans, one of
several brands produced by Castleberry.
--
Contributed by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Another possibly linked case that had only a short hospital stay.
San Diego county in California is in the extreme southwestern part of
the state. It can be found on a map at:
<http://pix.epodunk.com/locatorMaps/ca/CA_10813.gif> - Mod.LL]
